- tTheory of Religion in a Pragmatic Philosophical Theology -- tAcknowledgments -- tContributors -- tIndex of Names -- tSubject Index0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aThe Varieties of Transcendence traces American pragmatist thought on religion and its relevance for theorizing religion today. The volume establishes pragmatist concepts of religious individualization as powerful alternatives to the more common secularization discourse. In stressing the importance of Josiah Royce’s work, it emphasizes religious individualism’s compatibility with community. At the same time, by covering all of the major classical pragmatist theories of religion, it shows their kinship and common focus on the interrelation between the challenges of contingency and the semiotic significance of transcendence.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Mrz 2022) 0aPragmatism. 0aReligionxPhilosophy. 0aReligion--Philosophy. 4aPhilosophy & Theory. 4aReligion. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Movements / Pragmatism.2bisacsh  aCommunity.  aContingency.  aIndividualism.  aPhilosophy of Religion.  aPragmatism.  aSecularization.  amodernity.  areligion.  asemiotics.  atranscendance.1 aColapietro, Vincent, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCummings Neville, Robert, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDeuser, Hermann, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDeuser, Hermann, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aJoas, Hans, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJung, Matthias, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aJung, Matthias, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKestenbaum, Victor